itle elementor-size-default\">About Kaladharaa<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-7145ecc elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"7145ecc\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-fc6e186\" data-id=\"fc6e186\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1468c59 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"1468c59\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<style>\/*! elementor - v3.20.0 - 26-03-2024 *\/\n.elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-stacked .elementor-drop-cap{background-color:#69727d;color:#fff}.elementor-widget-text-editor.elementor-drop-cap-view-framed .elementor-drop-cap{color:#69727d;border:3px solid;background-color:transparent}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap{margin-top:8px}.elementor-widget-text-editor:not(.elementor-drop-cap-view-default) .elementor-drop-cap-letter{width:1em;height:1em}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap{float:left;text-align:center;line-height:1;font-size:50px}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap-letter{display:inline-block}<\/style>\t\t\t\t<p>Kaladharaa Dance is an established dance organization based in Utah &amp; Washington D.C., who\u2019s mission is to <br \/>promote and preserve the Indian classical across boundaries, focusing mainly on \u2018Kathak\u2019 which is one <br \/>amongst the eight Indian classical dance forms, with its origin from North India. <br \/><br \/>Nidhika Loomba &amp; Sonali Loomba are the artistic directors of this organization who have studied kathak <br \/>extensively under the guidance of their Guru\u2019s Sri Hari &amp; Smt. Chethana Hari , Internationally recognized <br \/>Kathak dance couple from Bangalore, India. <br \/><br \/>The duo, Nidhika &amp; Sonali have performed as soloist and duet\u2019s on National and International platforms such <br \/>as TEDx Salt Lake City \/ TEDx BentleyU , Kennedy Art Center- Washington DC, Wolf Trap \u2013 Virginia, Baltimore <br \/>Theater Project \u2013 Maryland, National Arts Center- Ottawa, Panteges Play house- Winnipeg, Korzo Theater- <br \/>Netherlands, Gandhi Center- Netherlands, Mus\u00e9e Guimet- Paris, \u00e9space Culturel Django Reinhardt- <br \/>Strasbourg. Hampi Utsav, Natyajanli Festival, Perur to name a few.<\/p><p>Their solo &amp; Collaborative works such as \u2018Anubhav- An Experience \u2019 , \u2018Aarambh- A beginning \u2019. \u2018Anhad \u2013 <br \/>Journey of a Seeker \u2019, \u2018Roots &amp; Rhythms \u2013 Exploring the kinship between Flamenco &amp; Kathak\u2019 are noteworthy. <br \/><br \/>Kaldharaa dance has trained over 200+ art enthusiast on the nuances of this ancient art form and continues to <br \/>do in order to serve their mission to spread awareness of this art form. Dancers range from age 6 \u201350, both male and female. Classes are a combination of Theory of History &amp; Culture of India and Kathak along with practical application. <br \/><br \/>The organization hosts a Bi-annual event known as \u2018Baithak\u2019 where every student learning with Kaladharaa is <br \/>given an opportunity to present Kathak in professional performing theatre set up.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-ddd